thread.title: Minister for Land Information to visit Mexico
thread.title_full: Minister for Land Information to visit Mexico

author: Fuseworks Media
title: Minister for Land Information to visit Mexico
text:
Fuseworks Media Monday, 26 October, 2015 - 15:47 
Land Information New Zealand Minister Louise Upston leaves today for an official visit to Mexico. Minister Upston will visit Mexico City, where she will give a keynote speech at the Open Government Partnership Summit. 
"New Zealand has a strong and internationally recognised history of open data and transparent government. The Open Data Barometer Report shows New Zealand as a world leader in government data available to citizens. 
"New Zealanders view data and information as key public assets - the release of which can play a significant role in driving innovation through better decision making, and the creation of new services, tools, and knowledge. 
"Attending this summit will allow me to share New Zealandâ€™s expertise and experience, and see what other countries are doing in this space." 
Minister Upston is due to return to New Zealand on 31 October.
